projects:
[{'title': 'Growing Kendo Federation of Kyrgyz Republic and Promoting Kendo within the country', 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2013}, 'end': {'month': None, 'day': None, 'year': None}}, 'description': 'As I became Senior Kendo Officer of Kyrgyz Republic in 2013, my primary goal was to start project of growing the federation within the country through different activities: fundraising, receiving donations, engaging in international competitions and taking part in Japanese festivals. 

The mission of the project was to promote Kendo in Kyrgyzstan, attract more people to join the federation and start engaging more with federations worldwide.

Through continuous communication with International Kendo Federation (IKF) and All Japan Kendo Federation (AJKF) in Japan, I was able to achieve a donation of 20 armour sets (10 new, 10 used) and 20 new bamboo swords for our federation.

The donation is worth approximately £10,500.

Three major teachers with extreme experience (8 dan senseis) visited Kyrgyz Republic in October 2016, providing seminar of 3 days long.

Kyrgyz Kendo Federation visited St. Petersburg (Russia) in June 2016 and was able to show its great team spirit and connecting with new clubs in Russia.

Total output (2013-2016): 3 competitions held in Kyrgyzstan (2013-2016), 2 seminars held in Kyrgyzstan, 3 visited competitions abroad, 6 festivals attended.

Attracted approximately: 20 new people into federation, more expected after armour being received in early 2017.', 'contributors': [{'type': 'standardizedContributor', 'first_name': 'Malika', 'last_name': 'Kenzhebaeva', 'name': None, 'headline': 'Finance & Operations Director at Whereby'}]}]
